			<p>
			






<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
Reply <a href="/eq/board/message?board.id=Veterans&message.id=170793#M170793">1</a> of 9
</span>

			<br><img src="/i/p.gif" width=1 height=6><br>
			<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
			
					Viewed 216 times<br>
					
			</span>
			
		</td>
		
		<td rowspan=2 bgcolor="#050A0E" width=1><img src="/i/p.gif" height=1 width=1 border=0 alt=""><br></td>
	
		<td colspan=2 class="msg_text_cell" width="100%" valign=top style="text-align: justify; 
		" 
			>
			So here is what I have gathered from reading the forums the past couple days.<br><br>1) A FULL rollback of everyone was impossible because every character is not backed up prior to a patch.  As a developer I somewhat understand that this is difficult (not impossible) due to the sheer volume of characters. <br>2) Rollbacks were issued to players who directly interacted with beta merchants<br>3) Rollbacks were issued to players who somehow came in contact with items from beta merchants.  It seems that some people were unaware they came in contact with these items.<br>4) Rollback points are different for each person.  This leaves me to believe that characters are backed-up on some sort of rolling schedule.  I have yet to find a claim of people being rolled back more the 3 days.<br>5) Some people are still missing items/plat/corpses/etc<br><br>Questions for the community:<br>1)  As a community would we accept a longer down time each patch to give the engineers enough time to do a full backup of every character on the server? <br>2)  If something like this happens again, is it acceptable to take the servers down and roll everyone back, provided that the backups were done just prior to the patch?  Even if this means more downtime?<br><br>Questions for the Devs/correspondants<br>1)  Could one of the dev's or correspondants post about how long a complete backup would take?  Are we looking at 4 hrs for backup + 4 hrs for patch?  More?<br>2)  I realize that longer patches will have different effects on different people, espicially those living in timezones on the other side of the world.  Being in the US, this is not much of an issue for me as I am typically at work during patch time.  I think that the AB server is the only &quot;Euro&quot; server left.  Could this server be brought down during a better time for the players of that server? <br><div></div><br><br>As a player base I am curious to see if we can provide some POSITIVE FEEDBACK to help ensure that this does not happen again.  If you are going to take the time out of your day to respond to this post, please make it constructive.  Let's try and have one thread with potential solutions to FIX the problem, rather then another one complaining about how SOE screwed up.<br><br><br>Thank you for your time.<br>	
		</td></tr>
		<tr>
		
		<td class="msg_date_cell" valign=bottom nowrap>
		<span style="font-size: 8pt; font-weight: normal;">
		 <span class=date_text>01-20-2006</span> <span class=time_text>09:46 PM</span>
		</span>
