			i think it's obvious that the developers at SoE have no regard for any suggestions their customers might make regardless of their merit. simple fix:<br>stop giving them your money. i do this all the time. i get bad service from a waitress i ask for the manager. if the manager treats me like the waitress does i get up and leave and never go back. send all those SoE punks packing. make them go find a job. and all this &quot;how can you hope someone gets fired over a GAME?&quot; crap... this GAME is why they HAVE A JOB! take it seriously. this isn't welfare or some government-subsidized program. you are RESPONSIBLE to the consumers that give you their money. in spite of the BS you present with your EULA threats, YOU are the vendor. WE are the consumers. you know... those people with money to spend? so print out your EULA over and over again on your little printer at home and after all of your customers have left take them to Krogers and see how many packages of hamburger they give you in trade 8)<br>no worries. the day Vanguard releases is the last day SoE ever gets any money from me. thank you SoE for twisting all of our arms. you don't appreciate your customers. perhaps you'll find looking for customers more satisfying than respecting the ones you have? /shrug<br>i don't care if you have customers or not. eventually YOUR jobs will also be farmed out to India. after the way you have treated us why should we care?<br><br>i don't generally get this worked up about problems in game. i actually want to apologize to veryone for the posts i've made over the last 2 days. but ya know, you made the mistake SoE. YOU screwed-up. not us. how come it's always your customers that pay for your incompetence? well i say enough is enough. it's time to find a new game provider that either appreciates it's customers more, or, one that has devs and programmers that dont keep repeating the same silly indiscretions over and over. maybe your people should be... flipping hamburgers, or driving a taxi, or any number of other things. personally, i think it's the suits. the morons with degrees in higher education running the show that are to blame. but then again i'm a truck driver. what would i know, right? my 145 IQ means nothing without a pedigree from a center of higher learning. i know one thing. if i do my job like you people at SoE do, i get fired. so i don't have the luxery of doing my job the way you people do yours. /shrug<br><br>you people have had Everquest for what? 4 years? it's obvious that you don't want it and that you wish we would all just cancel our subscriptions. well you don't have to ask me 63 times. 62 will work.<br>funny... i never got to play Everquest in it's early days. i've spent the last 3 years watching my game devolve into a circus sideshow. dumbed down to the point that it's no fun anymore and splintered into so many pieces that you can never find anyone to group with anymore. but inspite all of that, the original game was so good that people are STILL playing it. hanging on to what it used to be. i know i have. you must be proud SoE team. /cheer<br><div></div>	
